<subSubSection pageNumber="841" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="841">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="841">Note:</emphasis>
The application of this name has been uncertain but Nordenstam (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="841">Taxon</emphasis>
54: 552. 2005) argues that it applies correctly to the species known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Willk. ex J. J. Rodr. (1874)" authorityName="J. J. Rodr." authorityYear="1874" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rodriguezii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="841">S. rodriguezii</emphasis>
Willk. ex J.J. Rodr. (1874)
</taxonomicName>
. This species is sometimes treated as a synonym of the variable 
<taxonomicName authority="Poir. (1789)" authorityName="Poir." authorityYear="1789" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucanthemifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="841">S. leucanthemifolius</emphasis>
Poir. (1789)
</taxonomicName>
and in order to avoid displacement of the latter name (for those who favour a broad species concept), Nordenstam has proposed 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucanthemifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="841">S. leucanthemifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for conservation against 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="841">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1762" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="varicosus">S. varicosus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
